Here's the ViewModel using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (recommended) plus the XAML page with compiled bindings:

**ViewModel — `ProductDetailViewModel.cs`**

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace MyApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Replace with your actual data-fetching logic
        var product = await FetchProductAsync();

        Name = product.Name;
        Price = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulate network
        return ("Widget Pro", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties (with `PropertyChanged` raises) and a `LoadCommand` from the `[RelayCommand]` attribute.

**XAML Page — `ProductDetailPage.xaml`**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel"
             Title="Product Detail">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="20" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='Available: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product"
                Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Code-behind (DI-friendly)**

```csharp
namespace MyApp.Views;

public partial class ProductDetailPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailPage(ProductDetailViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `x:DataType` at the page root enables **compiled bindings** (8–20× faster, AOT-safe).
- `[ObservableProperty]` generates `INotifyPropertyChanged` plumbing automatically.
- `[RelayCommand]` on an `async Task` method generates `LoadCommand` with built-in `IsRunning` tracking.
- `PropertyChanged` is auto-marshalled to the UI thread, so assigning properties from `await` is safe.

Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding typos at build time.
